English version :

This is my tiny little IF (Interactive Fiction or text based game) created
for the Nouvim 3000 : https://itch.io/jam/fr-nouvim-3000-an-2020

This ADF version contains an intro image and a module. A big thank you
to Astrofra, author of these two pieces of art ! And I also wanted to thank
Hugo Labrande, who gave me an example of Inform code !
Thank you both !

Astrofra's website : https://fra.planet-d.net/
Astrofra on Twitter : https://twitter.com/astrofra

Hugo Labrande's website : https://hlabrande.fr/
Hugo Labrande on Twitter : https://twitter.com/hlabrande



This disk, compatible with Kickstart 1.3 and above, will launch PPShow for
the picture, BastyPlayer for the module and finally FrotzStdIO for the game
itself. Yes, Frotz can run on 1.3 in its "Standard Input Output" version !!

Information for 1.3 users : you must maximize the Shell window before playing!


But, if you are a Frotz user, you can use it to launch "Fenetre.z5" directly,
on Kickstart 2+, MorphOS, AROS, AmigaOS 4 or any other operating system
with Frotz or another Inform interpreter (Android, iOS, Windows, Linux, 
MacOS, PSP, Kindle, Psion 5, etc.).

Good game (it'll take you 10 minutes to finish it but I want to add more 
texts, and to offer a less abrupt end, or at least a more original ending!


